- Detailed sales insights imply a comprehensive breakdown of sales data for analysis and decision-making; 
- Customer information typically includes name, contact details, and purchase history; 
- Alphabetical ordering by customer information enables easy lookup and comparison of customer sales performance.

- 'best-selling clothing items' refers to the items with the highest total revenue in each region; 
- 'active region' means a region where is_active = 1;
- 'total revenue' is the sum of all revenue from the sale of an item in a region.

- "Top-selling" implies items with the highest quantity sold; 
- "Past month" refers to the last 30 days; 
- "Europe" corresponds to the region with the name 'EU' in the regions table.

- A "successful" item refers to an item with the highest total revenue; 
- "Past year" is calculated as the period from the current date minus one year; 
- An "active" item is one with the is_active flag set to 1.
